name: db initialise
info:
Initialises database at start of flow or whenever data needs to be reset/reloaded. Interfaces with `db controller`.

- Drops and recreates empty `snmp_devices` and `snmp_objects` tables.
- Optionally loads SNMP device and object data into database from global environment variable `global.env.SNMP_OBJECT_LIST` csv file. Defaults to `C:\ProgramData\node-red\projects\node-red-snmp-gateway\data\SNMPObjectList.csv`. csv should contain a list of all snmp objects, with the following the following headers:
 - DeviceName
 - OID
 - Server IP
 - Version
 - User
 - AuthPass
 - PrivPass
 - SecurityLevel
 - AuthMode
 - PrivMode
 - Community
 - FriendlyName

## Input

Triggered at start of flow.

## Output

`msg.payload` contains the response from SQLite node.

name: db controller
info:
Database controller node, interfaces with the SQLite DB (create/read/update/delete). All flows should interface with a `db controller` node rather than the `db` directly.

## Input

The input message requires the following data:

- `msg.action`: (string enum: `loadObjectList` | `loadDeviceList` | `updateValues` | `selectObjects` | `selectDevices` | `initialise` | `updateDeviceUpdated`) see below. The database action to carry out using the message.
- `msg.payload`: (array | object) SQL Query parameters to send to the `node-red-node-sqlite` node.

### Query parameters (optional)

- `msg.devicename`: filters the table by matching `devicename`.
  - `msg.devicename` may be a substring within the `devicename`, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-B"
  - `msg.devicename` may include "%" as a wildcard, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A%-PDU-A" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A2-PDU-A"

### msg.action

Defines the type of database action:

- `loadObjectList`: inserts data into `snmp_objects` table. Expects array of `snmp_objects` in `msg.payload`.
- `loadDeviceList`: inserts data into `snmp_devices` table. Expects array of `snmp_devices` in `msg.payload`.
- `updateValues`: updates `values` field in the `snmp_objects` table, or inserts new record if no matching devicename/oid exists. Expects either array of `snmp_objects` objects or single object in `msg.payload`.
- `selectObjects`: fetches object list from `snmp_objects`. Can filter by `devicename` using `msg.devicename` in input.
- `selectDevices`: fetches object list from `snmp_objects`. Can filter by `devicename` using `msg.devicename` in input.
- `initialise`: drops and recreates empty `snmp_objects` and `snmp_devices` tables.
- `updateDeviceUpdated`: updates `updated` field for device in `snmp_devices` table. Expects valid `msg.devicename`, updates `updated` field to `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP`.

## Output

`msg.payload` contains the response from SQLite node.

name: db updateValues
info:
Executes an insert or update query on the `db controller` in both the `snmp_objects` and `snmp_devices` table.

- `snmp_objects` table: Updates `value` and `tstr` field for a matching `devicename` and `oid` in the  (or inserts new record if no matching `devicename`/`oid`).
- `snmp_devices` table: Updates `updated` field for a matching `devicename` if it exists with the `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP`.

## Input

Input message requires snmp object data in the payload.

`msg.payload` must be either an object or an array of objects containing:

- `msg.devicename`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `msg.oid`: (string) SNMP OID
- `msg.value`: (string) object value
- `msg.tstr`: (string) SNMP object type

## Output

`msg.payload` contains response from sqlite node.

name: db selectObjects
info:
Queries `db controller` and returns a list of snmp objects from the `snmp_objects` table.

## Input
Triggered by any input. The input msg data is ignored and possibly overwritten.

### Query parameters (optional)

- `msg.devicename`: filters the table by matching `devicename`.
  - `msg.devicename` may be a substring within the `devicename`, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-B"
  - `msg.devicename` may include "%" as a wildcard, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A%-PDU-A" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A2-PDU-A"

## Output
`msg.payload` contains an array of device objects:

- `id`: (integer) primary key
- `devicename`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `oid`: (string) SNMP OID
- `User`: (string) device snmpv3 username
- `value`: (string) object value
- `tstr`: (string) SNMP object type
- `updated`: (datetime) datetime object values were last updated

name: db selectDevices
info:
Queries `db controller` and returns a list of snmp devices from the `snmp_devices` table.

## Input
Triggered by any input. The input msg data is ignored and possibly overwritten.

### Query parameters (optional)

- `msg.devicename`: filters the table by matching `devicename`.
  - `msg.devicename` may be a substring within the `devicename`, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-B"
  - `msg.devicename` may include "%" as a wildcard, eg `msg.devicename` = "T1-L00-DC1-A%-PDU-A" will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A2-PDU-A"

## Output
`msg.payload` contains an array of device objects:

- `DeviceName`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `ServerIP`: (string) snmp device hostname/IP address
- `Version`: (string) snmp version
- `User`: (string) device snmpv3 username
- `SecurityLevel`: (string enum: `AuthPriv` | `AuthNoPriv` | `NoAuthNoPriv` ) string snmpv3 security level
- `AuthMode`: (string enum: `MD5` | `SHA`) snmpv3 auth protocol
- `AuthPass`: (string) snmpv3 auth password
- `PrivMode`: (string enum: `AES` | `DES`) snmpv3 privacy protocol
- `PrivPass`: (string) snmpv3 privacy password
- `Community`: (string) snmp v1/v2 Community
- `updated`: (datetime) datetime object values were last updated

name: snmp3 fetch and save
info:
Fetches objects from a SNMPv3 device using the `snmp3 fetch values` node, then writes the response values to the database using the `db updateValues` node.

## Input

Input messages should contain the following objects:

- `msg.devicename`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `msg.host`: (string) snmp device hostname/IP address
- `msg.username`: (string) device snmpv3 username
- `msg.securitylevel`: (string enum: `AuthPriv` | `AuthNoPRiv` | `NoAuthNoPRiv` ) string snmpv3 security level 
- `msg.authmode`: (string enum: `MD5` | `SHA`) snmpv3 auth protocol 
- `msg.authkey`: (string) snmpv3 auth password
- `msg.privmode`: (string enum: `AES` | `DES`) snmpv3 privacy protocol 
- `msg.privkey`: (string) snmpv3 privacy password
- `msg.oid`: (string) list of comma seperated oids

## Output

`msg.payload` contains response from sqlite node.

name: snmp3 fetch values
info:
Fetches objects from a SNMPv3 device using the `node-red-node-snmp` fetcher node and returns the response. The node will select the correct snmpv3 configuration based on the input message.

## Input

Input messages should contain the following objects:

- `msg.devicename`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `msg.host`: (string) snmp device hostname/IP address
- `msg.username`: (string) device snmpv3 username
- `msg.securitylevel`: (string enum: `AuthPriv` | `AuthNoPriv` | `NoAuthNoPriv` ) string snmpv3 security level 
- `msg.authmode`: (string enum: `MD5` | `SHA`) snmpv3 auth protocol 
- `msg.authkey`: (string) snmpv3 auth password
- `msg.privmode`: (string enum: `AES` | `DES`) snmpv3 privacy protocol 
- `msg.privkey`: (string) snmpv3 privacy password
- `msg.oid`: (string) list of comma seperated oids

## Output

`msg.payload` contains an array of objects, as per the `node-red-node-snmp` fetcher node.

name: get snmp device oid list
info:
Queries `db` and gets list of snmp devices (and connection details) from `snmp_devices` table.
Then for each device, gets a list of its oids from `snmp_objects` table.
Prepares and splits into one message per device, ready to send to an `snmp3 fetch` or `snmp3 fetch and save` node.

## Input

Triggered by any input. The input msg data is ignored and possibly overwritten.

## Output

Output messages (one per snmp device) contains the following objects:

- `msg.devicename`: (string) snmp device name (used as id for saving values to db)
- `msg.host`: (string) snmp device hostname/IP address
- `msg.username`: (string) device snmpv3 username
- `msg.securitylevel`: (string enum: `AuthPriv` | `AuthNoPriv` | `NoAuthNoPRiv` ) string snmpv3 security level 
- `msg.authmode`: (string enum: `MD5` | `SHA`) snmpv3 auth protocol 
- `msg.authkey`: (string) snmpv3 auth password
- `msg.privmode`: (string enum: `AES` | `DES`) snmpv3 privacy protocol 
- `msg.privkey`: (string) snmpv3 privacy password
- `msg.oid`: (string) list of comma seperated oids

name: http serve xml
info:
- Listens on `/objects`, fetches data from `db selectObjects` node and returns XML parsed array of SNMP objects.
- Listens on `/devices`, fetches data from `db selectDevices` node and returns XML parsed array of SNMP devices.

## http query parameters (optional)

- `devicename`: filters by matching devicename. Applies to both `/objects` and `/devices` endpoints.
  - `devicename` may be a substring within the devicename, eg `?devicename="T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU"` will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-B"
  - `devicename` may include "%" as a wildcard, eg `?devicename="T1-L00-DC1-A%-PDU-A"` will return "T1-L00-DC1-A1-PDU-A" and "T1-L00-DC1-A2-PDU-A"

func:
// this query inserts a new record into snmp_oids table for each OID
// unless there is an existing record with the same devicename and oid,
// in which case this record is updated with the payload value and tstr
msg.topic = `
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO snmp_devices (
    devicename,
    ipaddress,
    version,
    securitylevel,
    user,
    authmode,
    authpass,
    privmode,
    privpass,
    community
)
VALUES (
    $devicename,
    $ipaddress,
    $version,
    $securitylevel,
    $user,
    $authmode,
    $authpass,
    $privmode,
    $privpass,
    $community
)
`;

msg.payload = msg.payload.map(item => [
    item.DeviceName, 
    item.ServerIP,
    item.Version,
    item.SecurityLevel,
    item.User,
    item.AuthMode,
    item.AuthPass,
    item.PrivMode,
    item.PrivPass,
    item.Community
]);

return msg;

name: create snmp_devices table
func:
msg.topic = `
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS snmp_devices (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    devicename TEXT,
    ipaddress TEXT,
    version TEXT,
    securitylevel TEXT,
    user TEXT,
    authmode TEXT,
    authpass TEXT,
    privmode TEXT,
    privpass TEXT,
    community TEXT,
    updated DATETIME,
    UNIQUE(devicename, ipaddress)
);
`;
return msg;
